This paper presents a neural implementation of a dependency parser, which falls under the natural language processing (NLP) domain. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses bidirectional LSTMs, which are a popular deep learning technique, suggesting that it could also fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses a dynamic oracle to mitigate error propagation, which is a technique commonly used in reinforcement learning, suggesting that it could also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the CoNLL 2017 UD Shared Task, which is a competition focused on NLP, further supporting the likelihood of cs.CL. Finally, the paper mentions the use of PoS tagging, which is a common technique in computer vision, suggesting that it could also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision).
